Introduction

Source: vignettes/seascapeR.Rmd
seascapeR.Rmd
library(seascapeR)

Get Seascape Dataset information

ERDDAP dataset info and date ranges for two available datasets: global_monthly and global_8day.

s_mo <- get_seascape_info() # default: dataset = "global_monthly"
s_8d <- get_seascape_info("global_8day")
s_mo
#> <ERDDAP info> noaa_aoml_4729_9ee6_ab54 
#>  Base URL: https://cwcgom.aoml.noaa.gov/erddap/ 
#>  Dataset Type: griddap 
#>  Dimensions (range):  
#>      time: (2003-01-15T12:00:00Z, 2020-11-15T12:00:00Z) 
#>      latitude: (-89.975, 89.975) 
#>      longitude: (-179.975, 179.975) 
#>  Variables:  
#>      CLASS: 
#>          Units: None 
#>      P: 
#>          Units: Punits
s_8d
#> <ERDDAP info> noaa_aoml_seascapes_8day 
#>  Base URL: https://cwcgom.aoml.noaa.gov/erddap/ 
#>  Dataset Type: griddap 
#>  Dimensions (range):  
#>      time: (2002-08-29T12:00:00Z, 2020-12-02T12:00:00Z) 
#>      latitude: (-89.975, 89.975) 
#>      longitude: (-179.975, 179.975) 
#>  Variables:  
#>      CLASS: 
#>          Units: None 
#>      P: 
#>          Units: Punits

s_mo_dates <- get_date_rng(s_mo)
s_8d_dates <- get_date_rng(s_8d)
s_mo_dates
#> [1] "2003-01-15" "2020-11-15"
s_8d_dates
#> [1] "2002-08-29" "2020-12-02"

Map Seascape image tiles

Plot a map of Seascape classes:

map_seascape_wms(s_mo_dates[2], ctr_lon = -81.3, ctr_lat = 24.5, ctr_dd = 10)

For now this is just using the global_monthly dataset. Note that the image tiles produces by the Web Map Server (WMS) do not contain the data, just tiled image.

Get Seascape data

Note that the monthly is a raster layer and 8day is raster stack for multiple dates.

r_monthly <- get_seascape_data(
  ctr_lon = -81.3, ctr_lat = 24.5, ctr_dd = 10, 
  dataset = "global_monthly", var = "CLASS", 
  date_beg = "2020-11-01", date_end = "2020-12-01")
#> info() output passed to x; setting base url to: https://cwcgom.aoml.noaa.gov/erddap/
r_monthly
#> class      : RasterLayer 
#> dimensions : 401, 401, 160801  (nrow, ncol, ncell)
#> resolution : 0.05, 0.05  (x, y)
#> extent     : -91.35, -71.3, 14.5, 34.55  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
#> crs        : +proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs 
#> source     : memory
#> names      : CLASS 
#> values     : 3, 27  (min, max)

r_8day <- get_seascape_data(
  ctr_lon = -81.3, ctr_lat = 24.5, ctr_dd = 10, 
  dataset = "global_8day", var = "CLASS", 
  date_beg = "2020-11-01", date_end = "2020-12-01")
#> info() output passed to x; setting base url to: https://cwcgom.aoml.noaa.gov/erddap/
r_8day
#> class      : RasterStack 
#> dimensions : 401, 401, 160801, 5  (nrow, ncol, ncell, nlayers)
#> resolution : 0.05, 0.05  (x, y)
#> extent     : -91.35, -71.3, 14.5, 34.55  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
#> crs        : +proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs 
#> names      : CLASS_2020.10.31, CLASS_2020.11.08, CLASS_2020.11.16, CLASS_2020.11.24, CLASS_2020.12.02 
#> min values :                3,                3,                3,                3,                3 
#> max values :               27,               28,               27,               27,               27

Map Seascape data

map_seascape_raster(r_monthly)

For raster stacks, you need to subset to a raster layer:

library(raster)
#> Loading required package: sp
map_seascape_raster(raster(r_8day, 1))

And another raster layer:

library(raster)
map_seascape_raster(raster(r_8day, 2))

Plot classes over time

r_mo_2019 <- get_seascape_data(
  ctr_lon = -81.3, ctr_lat = 24.5, ctr_dd = 10, 
  dataset = "global_monthly", var = "CLASS", 
  date_beg = "2019-01-01", date_end = "2020-01-01")
#> info() output passed to x; setting base url to: https://cwcgom.aoml.noaa.gov/erddap/

plot_seascape_ts(r_mo_2019)
